For $\lambda = 2$: Solve $(A - 2I)\vect{v} = \vect{0}$:
\[
\begin{bmatrix} 2 & -2 \\ 1 & -1 \end{bmatrix}\vect{v} = \vect{0}
\implies \vect{v} = t\begin{bmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \end{bmatrix}
\]

For $\lambda = 3$: Solve $(A - 3I)\vect{v} = \vect{0}$:
\[
\begin{bmatrix} 1 & -2 \\ 1 & -2 \end{bmatrix}\vect{v} = \vect{0}
\implies \vect{v} = t\begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{bmatrix}
\]
